OL,6,FIn exceptional circumstances this is
OL,7,Fnot a problem but it seems to be
OL,8,Fbecoming commonplace.
OL,10,FFriday night saw a good example of
OL,11,Fthis.
OL,13,FA repeat of Midsomer Murders pushed
OL,14,FNews at Ten back to 10.50pm. The same
OL,15,Fthing will happen this Friday. As far
OL,16,Fas I can recall, it was the first time
OL,17,Fsince 2004 when a routine scheduling
OL,18,Fdecision pushed the news past 10.30pm.
OL,20,FNeedless to say, the move seemed to
OL,21,Fboost the audience for the BBC News.
OL,3,CAre we slowly drifting from News at Ten
OL,4,Cto News at When again?
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G5/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
